Web?topicID=49.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Please consider consolidating</span><hr size=1> All good points. A larger guild would be beneficial to many people; however, I can see many of the current Raincallers being lost in the shuffle.<br>
<br>
The Raincallers has always been a guild of friends, both RL and people we've met online. It has, for the most part, been a low to mid lvl guild. I've seen many people leave over the last two years, some were encouraged to seek a higher lvl guild and others were driven out. Two of the current guilds in this Federation were initially populated by former members of The Raincallers. *Waves at Voice of Transcendence and Steeldragons* (It's good to see these friends together again.) Other former members have gone onto Mensa Dmorte and the Dark Legion. We even have former members of Legion of the Little Folk.<br>
<br>
We are all networked in one way or another already; however, we only have an alliance. The Raincallers will never go away! We have been around for over two years and are not going to end that any time soon.<br>
<br>
The question of merging with another guild has been brought up recently to us. We didn't merge with Mensa Dmorte or the Steeldragons. Basically there were members that stated they'd rather stop playing EQ than merge with another guild. (was nothing personal with any of the other guilds)<br>
<br>
A feeder guild might work. But what will we call it? How about.... Defiant Raindragons and Conspiring Legion Dmorte???? Probably just Federation of Povar. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The only bad thing about a feeder guild would be that many guilds would still lose the more lively members to another guild. Friend or foe, it'd still be another guild. And some players stay in guilds just because so-and-so is still in the guild.<br>
<br>
I'd support the 46 and up guild and would be willing to contribute my enchanter, necro and bard to it. However, Rizhao has to stay with the Raincallers.<br>
<br>
Rizhao Richang<br>
52nd Druidess of Tunare<br>
Head Bottlewasher<br>
The Raincallers <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000060><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/utraps.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Traps</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator of the Federation</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#70DB93>(10/29/01 3:07:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=49.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Please consider consolidating</span><hr size=1> I understand the tension that accompanies this idea. There is the psychic value of being in the same guild for a long time, as well as of being an officer.<br>
<br>
Consolidation does not involve &quot;leaving&quot; your friends. After my main left LoLF, I grouped with them more than I did prior to my departure. You also meet new friends in other guilds. Changing guilds is not like leaving Povar. A bigger problem is people who don't read the Message Boards daily, or even weekly.<br>
<br>
Getting a FoP roster together would be a great first step - but consolidating is the best way to go unless EVERYBODY at EVERY level reads the MBs daily and uses them to plan concrete XP hunts and gear raids all the time.<br>
<br>
The problem with a 46+ guild is the loss of the most valuable asset: brainpower. A 46+ guild would let us keep every guild in existence, but what kind of guilds would be left after the most experienced and active players left? They would be husks, the mood would be different, people might be more likely to play other games and play EQ less frequently. There's a trend away from EQ now. I'd love to see the server-counts again instead of the &quot;UP/DOWN&quot; indicator. Those of us that stay need to band together - and staying in a guild that has only a few people on at peak hours is not the best way to go IMO.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
A post-consolidation FoP might look like this:<br>
<br>
Guild 1: Dark Legion would get all evil races/classes of any level<br>
<br>
Guild 2: LoLF would get any short race of any level<br>
<br>
Guild 3: This is the tough one...<br>
<br>
1.  Would we fold all the smaller guilds into the largest one? <br>
2.  Would that be Mensa?<br>
3.  Would any officers be willing to give up the status symbol? You can still be a leader if you are not an officer. We could create status-ranks for ex-officers if necessary.<br>
4.  I suggested LoLF and Dark Legion stay intact because their identity involves RP based on race/class -- other guilds have more flexibility. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm3.showPrevMessage?topicID=49.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm3.showNextMessage?topicID=49.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=49.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm3.emailToFriend?topicID=49.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm3.threadControl?topicID=49.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/slate/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm3.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=49.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm3.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=49.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub70.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="federationofpovarfrm1">Federation Discussion Forum<option value="federationofpovarfrm3">Federation Raid Ideas<option value="fed